%20of%20the%20highest%20court%20in%20the%20land%20since%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20salary%2C%20as%20of%202026%2C%20is%20%24320%2C700.%20That's%20less%20than%20the%20president%20(%24400%2C000)%2C%20but%20more%20than%20the%20vice%20president%20(%24235%2C100)%20or%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20(%24223%2C500)%2C%20per%20the%20United%20States%20Courts%20and%20the%20Office%20of%20Personnel%20Management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it's%20potentially%20lower%20than%20the%20justices%20could%20earn%20in%20private%20practice.%20According%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20lawyers%20among%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20earners%20in%20their%20industry%20were%20paid%20more%20than%20%24239%2C200%20in%202024%2C%20excluding%20profits%20for%20partners%20and%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAn%20associate%20justice%20has%20a%20slightly%20lower%20salary%2C%20at%20%24306%2C600.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222347%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Associate%20Justices%20Amy%20Coney%20Barrett%2C%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%2C%20Ketanji%20Brown%20Jackson%2C%20and%20Elena%20Kagan%20pose%20at%20a%20courtesy%20visit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a876071fb3fcb42648e948%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAssociate%20Justices%20Amy%20Coney%20Barrett%2C%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%2C%20Ketanji%20Brown%20Jackson%2C%20and%20Elena%20Kagan%20pose%20at%20a%20courtesy%20visit.%3Cp%3ECollection%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20the%20United%20States%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAssociate%20justices%20are%20still%20well%20compensated%2C%20with%20salaries%20in%20the%20low%20%24300%2C000s%2C%20even%20if%20they%20make%20less%20than%20the%20chief%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDepending%20on%20how%20old%20they%20are%20and%20how%20long%20they've%20served%2C%20a%20justice%20could%20be%20eligible%20to%20receive%20their%20salary%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20lives.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222788%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Associate%20Justice%20Stephen%20Breyer%20sits%20during%20a%20group%20photo%20of%20the%20Justices%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%20on%20April%2023%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a876501fb3fcb42648e952%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222091%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAssociate%20Justice%20Stephen%20Breyer%20sits%20during%20a%20group%20photo%20of%20the%20Justices%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%20on%20April%2023%2C%202021.%3Cp%3EErin%20Schaff-Pool%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20receive%20a%20lifetime%20salary%2C%20you%20must%20retire%20at%20the%20age%20of%2070%20with%20at%20least%2010%20years%20of%20service%2C%20or%20at%20the%20age%20of%2065%20with%2015%20years%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20to%20receive%20this%20pension%2C%20retired%20justices%20in%20good%20health%20are%20still%20expected%20to%20remain%20somewhat%20active%20in%20the%20legal%20profession%2C%20such%20as%20serving%20on%20lower%20courts%2C%20completing%20administrative%20work%2C%20or%20working%20for%20a%20state%20or%20federal%20agency%2C%20per%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20Law%20Revision%20Counsel's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fuscode.house.gov%2Fview.xhtml%3Fpath%3D%2Fprelim%40title28%2Fpart1%2Fchapter17%26edition%3Dprelim%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Justices%20with%20disabilities%20are%20exempt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20government%20jobs%20that%20receive%20a%20lifetime%20pension%20that%20matches%20your%20final%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20not%20even%20the%20president%20gets%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt's%20perhaps%20the%20most%20secure%20job%20in%20the%20world%3A%20Becoming%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20justice%20is%20a%20lifetime%20appointment.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224158%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20American%20Supreme%20Court%20justice%20Oliver%20Wendell%20Holmes%20Jr%20(1841%20-%201935)%2C%20seated%20at%20his%20desk%2C%201924.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a876d7fd4fbd083f298453%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223119%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPortrait%20of%20American%20Supreme%20Court%20justice%20Oliver%20Wendell%20Holmes%20Jr%20(1841%20-%201935)%2C%20seated%20at%20his%20desk%2C%201924.%3Cp%3ELibrary%20of%20Congress%2FInterim%20Archives%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20arduous%20process%20and%20the%20culmination%20of%20decades%20of%20schooling%20and%20hard%20work%2C%20but%20once%20you're%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20you're%20on%20it%20for%20life%20(or%20until%20you%20retire).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnically%2C%20a%20justice%20can%20be%20impeached%2C%20but%20it's%20only%20happened%20once%20in%20US%20history.%20In%201804%2C%20Samuel%20Chase%20was%20impeached%20by%20the%20House%2C%20which%20accused%20him%20of%20acting%20in%20a%20partisan%20manner%20in%20trials.%20He%20was%20later%20acquitted%20by%20the%20Senate%20and%20remained%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20until%20his%20death%20in%201811.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJustices%20receive%20lifetime%20security%20from%20the%20US%20Marshals.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224476%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22U.S.%20Marshals%20stand%20guard%20as%20abortion%20rights%20protesters%20demonstrate%20outside%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Samuel%20Alito's%20home%20on%20June%2027%2C%202022%20in%20Alexandria%2C%20Virginia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8791ffd4fbd083f29848f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222984%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EU.S.%20Marshals%20stand%20guard%20as%20abortion%20rights%20protesters%20demonstrate%20outside%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Samuel%20Alito's%20home%20on%20June%2027%2C%202022%20in%20Alexandria%2C%20Virginia.%3Cp%3ETasos%20Katopodis%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20president%2C%20who%20receives%20lifetime%20protection%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresidents-first-ladies-secret-service-code-names%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESecret%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20receive%20lifetime%20protection%20from%20the%20US%20Marshals%2C%20according%20to%20the%20advocacy%20organization%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffixthecourt.com%2F2019%2F04%2Fusms-foia-suit-2%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFix%20the%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EActive%20justices%20receive%20full-time%20security%20protection%2C%20while%20retired%20justices%20may%20receive%20protection%20when%20it's%20deemed%20warranted%2C%20and%20justices%20can%20decline%20it%20if%20they%20choose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere%20are%20no%20financial%20limits%20to%20what%20gifts%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20justice%20can%20receive%2C%20as%20long%20as%20they%20publicly%20disclose%20them.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224992%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Clarence%20Thomas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a87ad1d3e2f1aef369fc01%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223328%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClarence%20Thomas.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Amis%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20disclosure%20laws%20apply%20to%20justices%2C%20but%20with%20some%20caveats.%20All%20federal%20employees%20(including%20judges)%20have%20to%20disclose%20%26quot%3Bincome%2C%20dividends%2C%20most%20capital%20gains%2C%20significant%20debts%2C%20the%20purchase%20or%20sale%20of%20land%2C%20and%20gifts%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brennancenter.org%2Four-work%2Fresearch-reports%2Fwhat-gifts-must-supreme-court-justices-disclose%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrennan%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20aren't%20beholden%20to%20the%20code%20of%20conduct%20for%20other%20federal%20judges%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BJudicial%20Conference's%20interpretations%20of%20the%20ethics%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201991%2C%20the%20justices%20agreed%20to%20follow%20these%20lower-court%20rules%2C%20but%20it%20was%20voluntary%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3EThen%2C%20in%202023%2C%20the%20Court%20adopted%20its%20own%20formal%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20for%20Justices%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20include%20a%20mechanism%20for%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20it's%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20legal%20gray%20area%20if%20they%20don't%20follow%20the%20code.%20On%20occasion%2C%20justices%20have%20been%20called%20out%20for%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fall-the-ethics-questions-hanging-over-the-supreme-court-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20than%20forthcoming%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20gifts%20and%20perks%20they%20receive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclarence-thomas-disclose-harlan-crow-jet-trip-hawaii-senator-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustice%20Clarence%20Thomas%3C%2Fa%3E%20faced%20ethics%20questions%20for%20failing%20to%20disclose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrips-justice-clarence-thomas-took-with-harlan-crow-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eluxury%20trips%20funded%20by%20billionaire%20GOP%20donor%20Harlan%20Crow%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20travel%20on%20his%20private%20jet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Thomas%20said%20he%20thought%20he%20didn't%20need%20to%20report%20the%20trips%20because%20he%20believed%20they%20were%20considered%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20hospitality%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20was%20friends%20with%20Crow.%20He%20later%20said%20he%20would%20comply%20with%20newer%2C%20stricter%20guidelines%20about%20personal%20hospitality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20not%20the%20only%20one%20who's%20received%20perks.%20In%202024%2C%20Justice%20Ketanji%20Brown%20Jackson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-justices-got-gifted-beyonce-tickets-photo-albums-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceived%20Beyonc%C3%A9%20tickets%3C%2Fa%3E%20worth%20almost%20%244%2C000.%20Jackson%20reported%20the%20tickets%20in%20her%20financial%20disclosure%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJustices%20also%20make%20money%20from%20faculty%20positions%20and%20book%20deals.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22From%20left%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20Justices%20Anthony%20Kennedy%2C%20John%20Roberts%20and%20Stephen%20Breyer%20take%20part%20in%20a%20procession%20to%20mark%20Harvard%20Law%20School's%20bicentennial%20in%20Cambridge%2C%20MA%20on%20Oct.%2026%2C%202017.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8aca6d3e2f1aef36a0239%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFrom%20left%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20Justices%20Anthony%20Kennedy%2C%20John%20Roberts%20and%20Stephen%20Breyer%20take%20part%20in%20a%20procession%20to%20mark%20Harvard%20Law%20School's%20bicentennial%20in%20Cambridge%2C%20MA%20on%20Oct.%2026%2C%202017.%3Cp%3EJessica%20Rinaldi%2FThe%20Boston%20Globe%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20earn%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20from%20teaching%20gigs%20at%20universities%2C%20although%20there%20is%20a%20cap%20on%20this%20outside%20pay%20of%20around%20%2430%2C000%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F27%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fsupreme-court-justices-book-deals.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Justice%20Neil%20Gorsuch%20was%20paid%20%2430%2C379%20for%20a%20two-week%20course%20in%20Portugal%20through%20George%20Mason%20University%2C%20per%20his%20financial%20disclosure%20report.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20Justices%20Brett%20Kavanaugh%20and%20Amy%20Coney%20Barrett%20each%20received%20%2431%2C815%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Notre%20Dame%20Law%20School%20for%20separate%20courses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20most%20lucrative%20thing%20for%20a%20justice%20to%20do%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-justices-got-gifted-beyonce-tickets-photo-albums-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrite%20a%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20cap%20to%20what%20they%20can%20earn%20here.%20Jackson%20received%20a%20%242%20million%20advance%20from%20Penguin%20Random%20House%20for%20her%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BLovely%20One%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20published%20in%202024.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20Gorsuch%20received%20%24250%2C000%20from%20HarperCollins%20for%20his%20legal%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BOver%20Ruled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEvery%20year%2C%20the%20justices%20get%20a%20three-month%20recess.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222661%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%20speaks%20at%20the%20Jefferson%20Awards%20Foundation%2043rd%20Annual%20National%20Ceremony%20on%20June%2018%2C%202015%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8770fd3e2f1aef369fba4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221996%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EU.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%20speaks%20at%20the%20Jefferson%20Awards%20Foundation%2043rd%20Annual%20National%20Ceremony%20on%20June%2018%2C%202015%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3ELarry%20French%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20The%20Jefferson%20Awards%20Foundation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20end%20of%20June%20to%20the%20first%20Monday%20in%20October%20every%20year%2C%20the%20Court%20is%20in%20recess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20justices%20still%20work%20during%20this%20time%2C%20they%20have%20more%20free%20time%20in%20the%20summer%20than%20they%20do%20when%20the%20court%20is%20in%20session.%20They%20do%20not%20have%20to%20be%20present%20at%20their%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20building%2C%20and%20some%20justices%20through%20history%20have%20taken%20advantage%20of%20that%20by%20visiting%20remote%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20escape%20from%20the%20work%20itself%2C%20and%20it%20finds%20its%20way%20to%20them%20wherever%20they%20travel%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupremecourthistory.org%2Fscotus-scoops%2Fstill-at-work-how-the-justices-spend-their-summer-months%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20Historical%20Society.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIn%20DC%2C%20the%20justices%20have%20spacious%20personal%20chambers%20and%20office%20space.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Justice%20Sandra%20Day%20O'Connor%20in%20her%20chambers%20at%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%205th%20October%201981%2C%20ten%20days%20after%20she%20became%20the%20first%20female%20Justice%20to%20serve%20on%20the%20Court.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8772c1fb3fcb42648e971%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221970%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJustice%20Sandra%20Day%20O'Connor%20in%20her%20chambers%20at%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%205th%20October%201981%2C%20ten%20days%20after%20she%20became%20the%20first%20female%20Justice%20to%20serve%20on%20the%20Court.%3Cp%3EDavid%20Hume%20Kennerly%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20Building%2C%20the%20personal%20chambers%20of%20each%20justice%20are%20secretive%2C%20and%20no%20photos%20are%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20each%20one%20gets%20their%20own%20space%20to%20run%20as%20they%20please%2C%20including%20room%20for%20their%20clerks%20and%20other%20administrative%20employees.%20The%20chambers%20can%20include%20libraries%2C%20ornate%20details%20such%20as%20wood%20paneling%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1975%2F03%2F16%2Farchives%2Fbehind-the-marble-beneath-the-robes-supreme-court.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efireplaces%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20Building%20also%20has%20a%20great%20library%2C%20a%20private%20basketball%20court%2C%20and%20a%20special%20dining%20room.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227868%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20seen%20on%20February%2020%2C%202026%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a87b34fd4fbd083f2984be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225248%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20seen%20on%20February%2020%2C%202026%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EHeather%20Diehl%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFamously%2C%20there's%20a%20basketball%20court%20on%20the%20fifth%20floor%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20building%2C%20aptly%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Highest%20Court%20in%20the%20Land.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clerks%20are%20mainly%20the%20ones%20taking%20advantage%20of%20the%20court%2C%20though%20justices%20have%20been%20known%20to%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20private%20dining%20room%20for%20justices%20to%20use%20when%20hearing%20cases.%20They%20make%20a%20point%20to%20eat%20lunch%20together%2C%20which%20helps%20ease%20tensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20wonderful%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjudicature.duke.edu%2Farticles%2Ftable-for-nine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJudicature%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018.%20%26quot%3BWe%20try%20to%20avoid%20controversy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJustices%20choose%20the%20cases%20they%20want%20to%20hear%2C%20giving%20them%20almost%20total%20control%20over%20their%20caseload.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224373%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20supporter%20of%20gay%20marriage%20waves%20his%20rainbow%20flag%20in%20front%20of%20the%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20April%2028%2C%202015%2C%20where%20cases%20are%20heard%20about%20the%20constitutional%20right%20of%20same%20sex%20marriage.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a87877d3e2f1aef369fbcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20supporter%20of%20gay%20marriage%20waves%20his%20rainbow%20flag%20in%20front%20of%20the%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20April%2028%2C%202015%2C%20where%20cases%20are%20heard%20about%20the%20constitutional%20right%20of%20same%20sex%20marriage.%3Cp%3EAstrid%20Riecken%20For%20The%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20rest%20of%20us%2C%20who%20have%20to%20listen%20to%20our%20bosses%20and%20sometimes%20do%20work%20we%20really%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Edon't%20feel%20like%20doing%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjustice-alito-reveals-how-the-court-makes-decisions-2015-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20justices%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20autonomy%20to%20hear%20whatever%20cases%20they%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20courts%20send%20cases%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20but%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20doesn't%20%3Cem%3Ehave%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20hear%20them%20%E2%80%94%20it%20typically%20reviews%20100%20to%20150%20of%207%2C000%20cases%20sent%20its%20way%20each%20year.%20For%20a%20case%20to%20be%20reviewed%2C%20four%20of%20the%20nine%20justices%20must%20vote%20to%20accept%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20typically%20chooses%20cases%20that%20%26quot%3Bcould%20have%20national%20significance%2C%20might%20harmonize%20conflicting%20decisions%20in%20the%20federal%20Circuit%20courts%2C%20and%2For%20could%20have%20precedent