C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20fall%2C%20my%20mother%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-rectal-cancer-rise-young-people-protect-yourself-lower-risk-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediagnosed%20with%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2C%20seemingly%20minutes%20later%2C%20my%20father%20had%20some%20heart%20problems%20and%20ultimately%20suffered%20a%20stroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20was%20inching%20toward%20simultaneously%20caring%20for%20my%20young%20kids%20and%20aging%20parents.%20Suddenly%2C%20I%20was%20squarely%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsandwich-generation-caregiving-kids-aging-parents-caring-for-myself-too-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esandwich%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20now%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20terrifying%20reality%20that%20my%20parents%20did%20not%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20how%20to%20spend%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-who-retired-years-ago-share-successes-of-retirement-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20where%20they%20plan%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249615b6f-6c62-4dc4-a0c3-ec4f845b5d7b%5C%22%3EMy%20parents%20had%20no%20retirement%20plans%20once%20they%20sold%20their%20house%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20only%20child%2C%20I%20have%20been%20aware%20that%20I%20might%20need%20to%20be%20more%20invested%20in%20my%20parents'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20prepared%20to%20feel%20like%20their%20therapist%2C%20estate%20planner%2C%20realtor%2C%20and%20case%20manager%20all%20in%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20father's%20unfortunate%20reality%20was%20that%20he%20had%20to%20retire%20while%20in%20the%20hospital%20recovering%20from%20his%20stroke.%20Like%20many%20men%2C%20my%20father%20struggles%20to%20find%20his%20identity%20outside%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20was%20home%20with%20my%20parents%20during%20my%20father's%20recovery%20and%20before%20my%20mother's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-cancer-innovations-asco-2025-exercise-as-drug-astra-zeneca-early-treatment-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%20treatment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20broached%20the%20subject%20of%20their%20retirement%20plan%20by%20asking%20them%20about%20the%20sale%20of%20their%20home.%20They%20had%20long%20lamented%20that%20they%20no%20longer%20wanted%20to%20maintain%20their%20home.%20However%2C%20I%20did%20not%20realize%20how%20little%20my%20parents%20had%20discussed%20what%20would%20happen%20beyond%20this%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20my%20mother%20and%20father%20recovered%2C%20they%20moved%20forward%20and%20sold%20their%20home%20in%20Florida.%20Shortly%20after%20that%2C%20they%20stayed%20near%20my%20family%20in%20Texas%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftravel%2Flong-term-airbnbs-monthly-rentals-sublet-faq%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-term%20Airbnb%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20soon%20realized%20they%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20settling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20since%20stayed%20in%2015%20Airbnbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d03ab137-a2b9-43f5-aa47-1e22b0e30c14%5C%22%3ETheir%20planless%20lifestyle%20has%20continued%20to%20create%20issues%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20like%20stability.%20I%20know%20that%20they%20don't%20like%20living%20out%20of%20suitcases.%20They%20often%20go%20to%20an%20Airbnb%20in%20a%20new%20city%20and%20immediately%20contact%20the%20host%20about%20shortening%20their%20stay%20or%20finding%20a%20different%20place%20because%20they%20don't%20like%20the%20area%20they%20are%20in.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAdditionally%2C%20they%20would%20rather%20have%20a%20plan%2C%20a%20home%20to%20call%20their%20own%2C%20and%20a%20city%20to%20set%20up%20some%20roots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20their%20Airbnb%20living%20doesn't%20make%20much%20sense%20to%20me.%20When%20I%20push%20them%20to%20find%20a%20long-term%20plan%2C%20I%20realize%20they%20aren't%20even%20having%20the%20conversation%20with%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20actual%20conversations%20only%20came%20to%20a%20head%20when%20my%20father%20landed%20in%20the%20hospital%20again%20while%20traveling.%20Ultimately%2C%20my%20father%20learned%20he%20would%20need%20extensive%20open-heart%20surgery.%20They%20ended%20up%20going%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hospital-inventory-management-advice-mayo-clinic-cleveland-clinic-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECleveland%20Clinic%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20staying%20at%20two%20different%20Cleveland%20Airbnbs%20during%20their%20six-week%20stay%2C%20which%2C%20while%20you%20are%20recovering%20from%20open-heart%20surgery%2C%20is%20not%20necessarily%20the%20best%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226499449b-de24-412a-9203-2b15693fd9e4%5C%22%3EWhen%20aging%20is%20avoided%2C%20it%20creates%20more%20issues%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20through%20all%20of%20these%20experiences%20with%20my%20parents%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20avoiding%20retirement%20conversations%20can%20be%20rooted%20in%20other%20issues%2C%20like%20not%20wanting%20to%20face%20our%20mortality%20or%20that%20we%20might%20disappoint%20other%20family%20members%20by%20making%20a%20clear%20decision%20for%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20like%20my%20parents%20don't%20have%20a%20will%20or%20aren't%20organized%2C%20and%20I%20am%20certainly%20lucky%20that%20they%20have%20saved%20diligently%20for%20their%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20not%20feel%20fortunate%2C%20however%2C%20about%20their%20lack%20of%20a%20concrete%20plan.%20As%20their%20only%20child%20with%20children%20of%20my%20own%2C%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20their%20future%20adds%20a%20layer%20of%20stress%20for%20me.%20I%20often%20worry%20about%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstayed-in-fifty-two-airbnbs-one-year-tips-booking-deals-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbnb%20accommodations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whether%20the%20roads%20nearby%20are%20well%20lit%2C%20and%20whether%20they%20have%20social%20support%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20suspect%20their%20decision%20to%20wing%20it%20has%20been%20driven%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20sidestep%20the%20discomfort%20of%20planning%20for%20one's%20golden%20years.%20By%20opting%20to%20stick%20with%20short-term%20rentals%20rather%20than%20anything%20more%20permanent%2C%20they%20avoid%20confronting%20their%20own%20individual%20desires%20%E2%80%94and%20the%20risk%20that%20they%20might%20not%20be%20in%20alignment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20am%20only%20in%20my%2040s%2C%20I%20am%20already%20working%20on%20a%20retirement%20plan.%20I%20am%20well%20aware%20that%20my%20children%20will%20have%20things%20to%20worry%20about%3B%20that%20just%20comes%20with%20the%20territory%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandparents-raising-grandchildren-aging-retirement-caregiving-custody-housing-financial-struggles-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaging%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20confronting%20the%20inevitability%20of%20aging%20and%20embracing%20a%20concrete%20plan%20for%20my%20retirement%20is%20a%20gift%20I%20am%20giving%20to%20my%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20honest%20conversations%20about%20making%20definitive%20plans%20is%20incredibly%20challenging%2C%20but%20it%20also%20has%20huge%20payoffs%3A%20a%20season%20of%20life%20rooted%20in%20desire%20and%20as%20much%20agency%20as%20this%20time%20can%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-parents-live-in-airbnbs-sold-house-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772971621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8b1ff1fb3fcb42648f0ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-parents-live-in-airbnbs-sold-house-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20parents%20retired%20early%20because%20of%20health%20issues.%20They%20decided%20to%20sell%20their%20house%20and%20have%20since%20lived%20in%2015%20Airbnbs%20across%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Vanessa%20Scaringi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-parents-live-in-airbnbs-sold-house-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20millionaire%20living%20in%20Washington.%20I'm%20happy%20to%20pay%20more%20in%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20it%20helps%20everybody.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221511%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20woman%20smiling.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a21118d3e2f1aef369b737%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221209%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWashington%20proposed%20a%20tax%20on%20millionaires%2C%20and%20millionaire%20Victoria%20Hattersley%20supports%20it.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Victoria%20Hattersley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EVictoria%20Hattersley%20is%20a%20retired%20millionaire%20who%20supports%20her%20state's%20proposed%20millionaire%20tax.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHattersley's%20state%20of%20Washington%20proposed%20a%209.9%25%20tax%20on%20income%20earned%20above%20%241%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHattersley%20believes%20that%20society%20is%20better%20off%20when%20everyone%20is%20doing%20well%20financially.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Victoria%20Hattersley%2C%20a%2070-year-old%20millionaire%20who%20lives%20in%20Mount%20Vernon%2C%20Washington%2C%20about%20the%20state's%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-millionaire-support-billionaire-wealth-tax-higher-taxation-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eproposed%20millionaire%20tax%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20The%20bill%20would%20create%20a%209.9%25%20tax%20on%20income%20earned%20over%20%241%20million.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20when%20I%20was%20a%20kid.%20I%20lived%20in%20Trumbull%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20which%20was%20a%20more%20affluent%20town%2C%20but%20we%20weren't%20the%20affluent%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friends%20were%20going%20shopping%20at%20the%20really%20fancy%20mall%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20go%20to%20the%20discount%20stores%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20grow%20up%20with%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20married%20very%20young%2C%20had%20children%20young%2C%20and%20was%20in%20some%20difficult%20circumstances%20for%20several%20years.%20I%20even%20ended%20up%20having%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrocery-budgets-food-bank-assistance-how-mom-feeds-family-texas-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ego%20to%20food%20banks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20I%20understand%20hard%20that%20is%20and%20how%20stressful%20that%20kind%20of%20living%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Estarted%20my%20career%20in%20Boston%20when%20I%20moved%20back%20to%20be%20with%20my%20family.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20leverage%20some%20of%20the%20experience%20that%20I%20had%20back%20in%20Washington%20and%20started%20working%20at%20the%20AIDS%20Clinical%20Trials%20Group%20at%20the%20Harvard%20School%20of%20Public%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20in%20AIDS%20research%20and%20eventually%20met%20my%20husband%20%E2%80%94%20my%20last%20and%20most%20wonderful%20husband%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20the%20head%20of%20the%20biostatistics%20group%20at%20the%20statistical%20and%20data%20analysis%20center%20who%20did%20the%20clinical%20trials%20for%20AIDS%20research.%20I%20was%20on%20the%20admin%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20got%20married%2C%20and%20both%20of%20us%20had%20kids%2C%20so%20we%20needed%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20income%20than%20what%20academia%20could%20afford.%20We%20both%20went%20to%20the%20pharmaceutical%20industry%2C%20where%20I%20had%20a%2020-year%20career%20%E2%80%94%20he%20had%20a%20longer%20career%20because%20he%20went%20over%20there%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20stock%20options%20in%20the%20pharma%20industry%2C%20you%20make%20money%2C%20you%20invest%20it%2C%20and%20then%20you%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-buy-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoney%20on%20the%20investments%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20stock%20market's%20been%20very%20kind%2C%20and%20so%20that's%20where%20we%20made%20our%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d94aa5dd-39d9-44a8-9bcd-8c9bed9cb7cd%5C%22%3EI%20pulled%20myself%20up%20by%20my%20bootstraps%2C%20but%20not%20everyone%20should%20have%20to%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20at%20both%20ends%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecoming-millionaire-lost-friendships-trust-loneliness-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBecoming%20a%20millionaire%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20definitely%20not%20as%20simple%20as%20pulling%20yourself%20up%20and%20just%20doing%20the%20hard%20work.%20There's%20so%20much%20else%20that%20factors%20in%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20lot%20of%20luck.%20I%20got%20lucky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20me%20mad%20when%20people%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20did%20it%2C%20so%20you%20can.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20have%20that%20same%20attitude.%20Then%2C%20when%20I%20was%20going%20through%20life%2C%20gaining%20more%20experience%2C%20seeing%20very%20capable%20people%20try%20and%20try%20and%20work%20hard%20at%20getting%20jobs%2C%20and%20the%20jobs%20aren't%20there%2C%20or%20they're%20not%20recognized%20for%20this%20or%20that%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20I%20realized%20it's%20definitely%20not%20that%20simple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENobody%20%3Cem%3Edoesn't%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewant%20to%20be%20well%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20should%20be%20able%20to%20get%20wealthy%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20that.%20The%20thing%20is%2C%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmassachusetts-millionaire-pays-wealth-tax-considers-moving-to-florida-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epay%20your%20fair%20share%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20taxes.%20That's%20the%20bottom%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESociety%20and%20culture%20are%20better%20off%20when%20people%20are%20doing%20well%2C%20when%20people%20can%20work%20and%20they%20can%20have%20healthcare%20and%20have%20their%20kids%20go%20to%20daycare.%20When%20that%20happens%2C%20they%20produce%20more%20and%20that%20produces%20more%20taxes%20for%20what%20we%20need%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20just%20a%20healthier%20way%20of%20structuring%20society%20than%20holding%20people%20down%20and%20taxing%20people%20into%20poverty%2C%20while%20people%20at%20the%20very%20high%20end%20are%20not%20contributing%20their%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d49584d8-38fc-4da2-9cbf-52504a2b1f83%5C%22%3EThe%20new%20bill%20in%20my%20state%20would%20only%20affect%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20residents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWashington%20has%20one%20of%20the%20most%20regressive%20tax%20codes%20in%20the%20country.%20It%20impacts%20lower-income%20folks%20more%20than%20higher-income%20folks.%20They%20pay%20a%20higher%20share%20of%20their%20money%20because%20of%20the%20tax%20structure.%20Plus%2C%20those%20with%20more%20money%20have%20more%20opportunities%20to%20hire%20financial%20advisors%20who%20can%20help%20them%20find%20tax%20loopholes%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20legislation%20in%20Washington%20is%20a%209.9%25%20tax%20on%20income%20%E2%80%94%20not%20under%20stocks%20or%20anything%20%E2%80%94%20over%20%241%20million%20a%20year%20starting%20in%202028%2C%20and%20then%20the%20first%20payments%20would%20be%20in%202029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20only%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20people%20in%20Washington%20state%20who%20would%20be%20subject%20to%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recognize%20that%20as%20you%20gain%20more%20wealth%2C%20you%20keep%20looking%20around%20the%20corner%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20if%20I%20had%20more%2C%20I%20could%20do%20this.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20lose%20any%20of%20my%20money%20because%20I'm%20already%20looking%20at%20this%20new%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20it%20is%20a%20syndrome%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoney-dysmorphia-why-wealthy-people-dont-feel-rich-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexcessive%20wealth%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20conversations%20around%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f49f2a04-8db5-4b39-8f57-4cabba575d83%5C%22%3EEveryone%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20wealthy%20paying%20their%20fair%20share%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20volunteering%20in%20the%20democracy%20space%20for%20many%20years%20prior%20to%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20in%20the%20democracy%20ecosystem%20space%20and%20transpartisan%20space%2C%20trying%20to%20strengthen%20our%20civic%20engagement%20across%20the%20country%20with%20a%20couple%20of%20different%20organizations%20doing%20that%2C%20as%20well%20as%20with%20the%20Patriotic%20Millionaires%20in%20my%20volunteer%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20just%20believe%20that%20there%20is%20excessive%20wealth%2C%20and%20it's%20getting%20worse%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20only%20going%20to%20get%20worse%20in%20very%20quick%20fashion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20inequality%20is%20so%20drastic.%20We%20look%20back%20at%20history%2C%20and%20we%20see%20that%20this%20is%20where%20cultural%20instability%2C%20social%20instability%2C%20and%20economic%20instability%20happen%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20not%20healthy%2C%20and%20there%20are%20no%20barriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20are%20wealthy%20just%20can't%20conceive%20this%20kind%20of%20life%20where%20you're%20trying%20to%20take%20care%20of%20your%20kids%2C%20you're%20working%20jobs%2C%20you're%20just%20trying%20to%20pay%20the%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20all%20most%20people%20want%20to%20do%3B%20they%20want%20to%20pay%20their%20bills.%20They%20would%20love%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-to-buy-a-house-step-by-step-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eown%20a%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They'd%20like%20to%20maybe%20take%20a%20vacation%2C%20or%20they%20want%20to%20put%20their%20kids%20in%20a%20decent%20daycare.%20The%20stress%20level%20of%20not%20knowing%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20your%20rent%2C%20your%20car%20note%2C%20or%20your%20heat%20is%20awful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20are%20we%20taxing%20people%20into%20a%20place%20where%20it's%20impossible%20for%20them%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20situation%20they're%20in%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20see%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20excessive%20wealth%20inequality%20that's%20happening%20in%20our%20society%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20dangerous%20for%20all%20of%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20bill%20would%20do%20would%20be%20to%20provide%20people%20perhaps%20with%20some%20tax%20holidays%20and%20help%20small%20businesses.%20The%20governor%20is%20very%20clear%3A%20We%20need%20to%20put%20money%20back%20into%20people's%20pockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20something%20that%20is%20just%20important%20for%20individuals.%20It%20is%20important%20for%20individuals%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20important%20for%20everyone%3A%20for%20our%20entire%20society%2C%20for%20our%20country%2C%20that%20we%20address%20this%20inequality%2C%20because%20it%20can't%20continue.%20We%20will%20have%20significant%20societal%20and%20cultural%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20just%20passionate%20about%20helping%20the%20people%20who%20want%20to%20do%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20just%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwashington-millionaire-tax-wealthy-support-paying-more-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772970601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a2137f1fb3fcb42648a50d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwashington-millionaire-tax-wealthy-support-paying-more-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Victoria%20Hattersley%2C%20a%20Washington%20millionaire%2C%20says%20she's%20happy%20to%20pay%20more%20in%20taxes%20as%20part%20of%20her%20state's%20proposed%20millionaire%20tax.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwashington-millionaire-tax-wealthy-support-paying-more-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20hasn't%20the%20Iranian%20regime%20collapsed%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772968620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F26%2F03%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-iran-khamenei-supreme-leader_7185992.jpg%3F20260308120241%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhy-hasnt-the-iranian-regime-collapsed-13516892%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nine%20days%20into%20the%20war%2C%20the%20Iranian%20regime%20remains%20intact%20and%2C%20at%20least%20to%20some%20degree%2C%20in%20control%20of%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhy-hasnt-the-iranian-regime-collapsed-13516892%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20hasn%26amp%3B%238217%3Bt%20the%20Iranian%20regime%20collapsed%3